text: Dulo Properties LTD House Rules and Obligation in addition to the contract. The Tenant understands he/she is renting a room within a shared accommodation along with other roommates. Thus, the Tenant agrees to be bound by the following general rules ensuring respectful and pleasant co-habitation. Any breach of the following will cause in an official warning, and in two warnings we will proceed with legal eviction procedures as per contract 1. Overnight guests. 1.1. Each roommate has

the right to have overnight guests for a period of maximum of five days in a calendar month. 1.2. If the overnight guests cause any disturbance or nuisance to the other roommates, the landlord has the right to demand the leaving of the guests immediately. 2. Parties/Entertaining. 2.1. Parties and social get-togethers are allowed as long as they do not disturb in any way the other tenants and neighbours. 2.2. If the other roommates express any grievances the party/get-together must be

terminated immediately. The same goes if any of the neighbours complain. 3. Household upkeep. 3.1. The tenants are responsible for their own personal rooms and are also responsible for cleaning the common area after themselves, so the other occupants can enjoy the accommodations in a pleasant and clean atmosphere (that means, but is not exhaustive: no dishes or other utensils left in the sink overnight; no leaving of stains on the tables or chairs; no leaving of silverware and other perso

nal belongings in areas that other tenants may wish to also use in case that they have been vacated by the previous user (tenant) of the common area). 3.2. If a tenant causes continuous disturbance and does not comply with the above, there will be an official warning. 3.3. Noise level should be kept at a minimum during the hours of 9pm to 8amam and during other times courtesy should be used to the other tenants. Friday and Saturday nights may allow for social get-togethers where that doe

s not cause irritation to the other occupiers. 3.4. Smoking in the enclosed premises is not allowed under any circumstances! 3.5. Alcohol is allowed, but drunken disturbance will not be tolerated under any circumstances. 4. These Roommate Obligations and Rules should be followed not only in form, but also in spirit. The assured pleasant living of all the occupants of the premises is our main goal and objective. If any issues arise which cause disturbance for the neighbours or other occup

ants, then the perpetrator will receive an official warning, after two such warnings, the same perpetrator will be subject to eviction with termination and voidance of the Agreement. 5. Please only use cupboards in the kitchen that have been allocated to your room. 6. This is a shared property so please have respect for the other tenants in the house and their belongings.
